subSubSection.paragraph:
Ecology . Rocky and mixed rock-rubble-sand intertidal and shallow subtidal, often on rocky reefs rich in rocks encrusted by sponges and coralline algae, known depth range: typically 0–12 m , exceptionally 44 m ; under rocks and coral debris, in crevices of dead coral heads (especially
Pocillopora
) and other shelters ( Gore 1982 ; present study).
